:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Franklyn was born in 1458, in Wiltshire, England, his father, William Francklyn, was 23 and his mother, Ann Babe Smith, was 23. He had at least 1 daughter with Jane Bathurst. He died in 1520, in Wiltshire, England, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1458–1520":"1458–1520","1465–1535":"1465–1535","1488–1559":"1488–1559","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1435–1485":"1435–1485","1458":"1458","1535":"1535","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1488":"1488","1520":"1520","1465":"1465","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Bynall, Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, England","Bynall, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1458–1520":"1458–1520","1465–1535":"1465–1535","1488–1559":"1488–1559","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1435–1485":"1435–1485","1458":"1458","1535":"1535","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1488":"1488","1520":"1520","1465":"1465","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Bynall, Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, England","Bynall, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1458–1520":"1458–1520","1465–1535":"1465–1535","1488–1559":"1488–1559","1435–1500":"1435–1500","1435–1485":"1435–1485","1458":"1458","1535":"1535","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1488":"1488","1520":"1520","1465":"1465","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre","Bynall, Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre","Bynall, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas Franklyn est né en 1458, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, son père, William Francklyn, avait 23 ans et sa mère, Ann Babe Smith, avait 23 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Jane Bathurst. Il 